The paper focuses on learning local descriptors for 3D reconstruction tasks, which is a common problem in computer vision and robotics. The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and geometry constraints from multi-view reconstructions suggests that the paper is likely to be related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The integration of geometry constraints also suggests that the paper may be related to robotics (cs.RO) and graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the use of learned descriptors for practical integration in Structure-from-Motion (SfM) pipelines suggests that the paper may also be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
